
Overview of noun trumpeter

The noun trumpeter has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) trumpeter, cornetist -- (a musician who plays the trumpet or cornet)
2. herald, trumpeter -- ((formal) a person who announces important news; "the chieftain had a herald who announced his arrival with a trumpet")
3. trumpeter -- (large gregarious crane-like bird of the forests of South America having glossy black plumage and a loud prolonged cry; easily domesticated)
4. trumpeter, trumpeter swan, Cygnus buccinator -- (large pure white wild swan of western North America having a sonorous cry)
